# Learned: docs

Auto-maintained by the `agents-memory-updater` subagent. New bullets are
capped at 200 chars and 12 bullets per section. The existing entries below
were harvested verbatim from `AGENTS.md` during the one-time context
cleanup; they may exceed the 200-char cap.

## Learned User Preferences

- Fumadocs docs nav must avoid label-stutter (e.g. 'Guides > Guides') — May 2026 best practice flattens nested sidebar groups; review `docs/policy/documentation-policy.md` before reshaping nav.
- In-doc links to other Fumadocs pages must use Fumadocs route helpers, not hand-rolled `/docs/guides/...` strings — the latter silently rot when route groups move.
- Page-level Copy/Copy-Markdown helpers render in the Fumadocs page header (mirroring our docs theme), never as a bottom-right sticky button.
- Typedoc/API Reference styling must match Shiki syntax colors exactly — monochrome reference text is a UX smoking gun that hides type/identifier distinctions.

